{
  "id": "L19",
  "title": "Visiting a Dutch Friend's Home",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you'll learn how to handle a visit to a Dutch friend's house. It's common in the Netherlands to bring a small gift!"
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V01",
      "data": {
        "De bloemen": "The flowers"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V02",
      "data": {
        "De wijn": "The wine"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V03",
      "data": {
        "Het huis": "The house"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hoi",
        "meaning": "Hi"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dit is voor jou",
        "meaning": "This is for you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank je wel",
        "meaning": "Thank you very much"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Wat een mooi huis!",
        "meaning": "What a nice house!"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "huis",
        "phonetic": "[ɦœys]",
        "tip": "The Dutch 'ui' sound is tricky. It's a bit like gliding from the 'u' in 'burn' to the 'ee' in 'see'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_S01",
      "title": "Arriving at a Friend's House",
      "setting": "You are at the front door of your friend Lars's house. He opens the door.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet your friend",
          "chatbot_message": "Hoi! Welkom!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Give your gift",
          "chatbot_message": "Oh, wat leuk! Dank je wel."
        },
        {
          "title": "Compliment their home",
          "chatbot_message": "Dank je. Kom binnen!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great! Now you're inside. Your friend will probably offer you something to drink. The standard options are `koffie` (coffee) or `thee` (tea)."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V04",
      "data": {
        "De koffie": "The coffee"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V05",
      "data": {
        "De thee": "The tea"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V06",
      "data": {
        "De keuken": "The kitchen"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ja, graag",
        "meaning": "Yes, please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Een kopje...",
        "meaning": "A cup of..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Alsjeblieft",
        "meaning": "Please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hoe was je week?",
        "meaning": "How was your week?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Kan ik helpen?",
        "meaning": "Can I help?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "keuken",
        "phonetic": "[ˈkøː.kə(n)]",
        "tip": "The 'eu' sound is also typically Dutch. It's like the 'oo' in the English word 'book', but with more rounded lips."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_S02",
      "title": "Making Small Talk",
      "setting": "You are now in the living room. Lars asks if you want a drink.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Accept a drink and state your preference",
          "chatbot_message": "Ga zitten. Wat wil je drinken? Ik heb koffie en thee."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask how their week was",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké, een kopje thee. Ik ga naar de keuken. Mijn week was goed, dank je."
        },
        {
          "title": "Offer to help",
          "chatbot_message": "Nee, dank je. Blijf lekker zitten."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "The word `gezellig` is very important in Dutch culture. It means cozy, fun, or a pleasant atmosphere. Saying `Het was gezellig` is a great way to compliment your host."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V07",
      "data": {
        "De avond": "The evening"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19_V08",
      "data": {
        "Laat": "Late"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Het is al laat",
        "meaning": "It is already late"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik moet gaan",
        "meaning": "I have to go"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E12",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank je wel voor de leuke avond",
        "meaning": "Thank you for the nice evening"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E13",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Graag gedaan",
        "meaning": "You're welcome"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19_E14",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Doei",
        "meaning": "Bye (informal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "gezellig",
        "phonetic": "[ɣəˈzɛləx]",
        "tip": "The 'g' sound in Dutch is made in the back of your throat. It's a soft, scraping sound, not like the 'g' in 'go'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19_S03",
      "title": "Saying Goodbye",
      "setting": "You've had a nice evening, but now it's time to leave.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Say that it's getting late",
          "chatbot_message": "Oh, oké. Jammer."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank your friend for the evening",
          "chatbot_message": "Graag gedaan. Ik vond het ook gezellig."
        },
        {
          "title": "Say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "Doei! Tot de volgende keer!"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}